HEADWORD: Lithocyst
<hw>Lith"o*cyst</hw> <pr>(l⟦icr⟧th"⟦osl⟧*s⟦icr⟧st)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Litho-</ets> + <ets>cyst</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>A sac containing small, calcareous concretions
(<xex>otoliths</xex>). They are found in many Medus⟦ae⟧, and other
invertebrates, and are supposed to be auditory organs.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Lithodome</ent>⟦br⟧
